WEBVTT

02:16.403 --> 02:18.539
- Hello?
- <i>Hello, Meg?</i>

02:18.573 --> 02:19.941
<i>It's me,</i>

02:19.974 --> 02:21.208
Kathy Madison.

02:22.275 --> 02:23.645
I hope you're awake, girl.

02:24.812 --> 02:26.547
<i>It's almost midday,
for God's sake.</i>

02:26.581 --> 02:27.715
Of course, I'm awake.

02:28.148 --> 02:29.984
Barely, I'd say.

02:30.018 --> 02:32.820
Listen, Meg, I need you
in my office in about an hour.

02:32.854 --> 02:34.187
Can you make that?

02:35.355 --> 02:36.423
Of course.

02:36.456 --> 02:37.491
But why?

02:37.525 --> 02:38.826
What's up?

02:38.860 --> 02:40.360
I'll be waiting.

02:40.394 --> 02:41.395
Don't be long.

03:06.353 --> 03:08.823
<i>♪ Naked telephone poles</i>

03:08.856 --> 03:10.024
<i>♪ Can't describe</i>

03:10.058 --> 03:13.393
<i>♪ The way I'm feeling
about you tonight</i>

03:13.427 --> 03:16.964
<i>♪ And a feeling on my back
Like an old brown jacket</i>

03:16.998 --> 03:20.034
<i>♪ Like to stay in school
but I just can't hack it</i>

03:20.068 --> 03:21.903
<i>♪ And I'm out on the street</i>

03:21.936 --> 03:23.738
<i>♪ And I'm feeling like dirt</i>

03:23.771 --> 03:25.272
<i>♪ She's afraid to get married</i>

03:25.305 --> 03:26.741
<i>♪ Because she knows
it's going to hurt</i>

03:26.774 --> 03:28.275
<i>♪ And I say</i>

03:28.308 --> 03:29.977
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh</i>

03:30.011 --> 03:32.814
<i>♪ There's the last
of the rock stars</i>

03:32.847 --> 03:34.882
<i>♪ And me and you</i>

03:34.916 --> 03:37.417
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh</i>

03:37.451 --> 03:39.286
<i>♪ Rock 'n roll
is here to stay</i>

03:39.319 --> 03:41.488
<i>♪ But who will be
left to play</i>

03:50.631 --> 03:54.468
<i>♪ Well, I dreamed
I saw the king in a '53 Chevy</i>

03:54.502 --> 03:56.436
<i>♪ Had a band on his mind</i>

03:56.470 --> 03:57.872
<i>♪ And his hands
looked pretty heavy</i>

03:57.905 --> 04:01.475
<i>♪ And he rolled down his window
I guess to say hi</i>

04:01.509 --> 04:03.077
<i>♪ But I couldn't see his face</i>

04:03.111 --> 04:04.846
<i>♪ 'Cause of
the purple haze inside</i>

04:04.879 --> 04:08.281
<i>♪ He was born to be the king,
he was born to be the man</i>

04:08.315 --> 04:09.951
<i>♪ And he died
though he was holy</i>

04:09.984 --> 04:11.351
<i>♪ Although I doubt
he'd understand</i>

04:11.384 --> 04:12.787
<i>♪ When I say</i>

04:12.820 --> 04:14.822
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh</i>

04:14.856 --> 04:17.457
<i>♪ There's the last
of the rock stars</i>

04:17.491 --> 04:19.392
<i>♪ And me and you</i>

04:19.426 --> 04:22.029
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh</i>

04:22.063 --> 04:23.598
<i>♪ Rock 'n roll
is here to stay</i>

04:23.631 --> 04:26.299
<i>♪ But who will be
left to play</i>

04:27.935 --> 04:29.871
<i>♪ Yeah, yeah</i>

04:32.640 --> 04:34.509
<i>♪ Adolescent pre-drug habit</i>

04:34.542 --> 04:35.977
<i>♪ If it means guitar
he's gotta have it</i>

04:36.010 --> 04:37.745
<i>♪ And you got your ax
and you got your group</i>

04:37.779 --> 04:39.514
<i>♪ And your old man thinks
it's a waste of loot</i>

04:39.547 --> 04:41.549
<i>♪ And you wait all week
for a Sullivan show</i>

04:41.582 --> 04:43.350
<i>♪ And you see that's right
where you wanna go</i>

04:43.383 --> 04:45.119
<i>♪ And your homework
is never complete</i>

04:45.153 --> 04:46.453
<i>♪ You don't care</i>

04:46.486 --> 04:48.923
<i>♪ 'Cause you have
got the beat... ♪</i>

04:51.726 --> 04:52.727
Hey, Meg.

04:53.227 --> 04:54.461
Glad you made it.

04:55.096 --> 04:56.864
Hi, Kathy is in there?

04:56.898 --> 04:58.766
- Can I go in?
- One moment, please.

05:05.405 --> 05:07.074
Ms. Madison?

05:07.108 --> 05:09.043
- Meg is here.
- Send her in.

05:15.448 --> 05:16.449
Hi, Kathy.

05:19.887 --> 05:22.489
Isn't that The Words
on the cover there?

05:22.523 --> 05:25.560
Funny, I was just listening
to them.

05:25.593 --> 05:28.029
He was like a god
once upon a time.

05:28.062 --> 05:29.864
A fallen god, I'm afraid.

05:29.897 --> 05:32.166
Well, a rock god, nonetheless.

05:32.200 --> 05:34.769
In fact, The Words
are more popular now

05:34.802 --> 05:36.571
than when Jake Lion was alive.

05:37.839 --> 05:39.774
Do you remember
that article you wrote

05:40.675 --> 05:42.910
about The Words

05:42.944 --> 05:45.980
and all that rock music
from the '70s

05:46.013 --> 05:48.583
when I first took over
the magazine from my father?

05:49.650 --> 05:51.652
Well, I dug it out of the vault.

05:51.686 --> 05:54.155
Wow. That was a long time ago.

05:54.188 --> 05:56.489
My first piece
for <i>Rolling Stone.</i>

05:58.526 --> 06:01.829
Are you still into Jake Lion
and The Words?

06:01.863 --> 06:04.065
Like any rock lover should.

06:04.098 --> 06:05.398
You want to meet him?

06:05.900 --> 06:07.201
Are you nuts?

06:07.235 --> 06:09.737
He has been dead
for over 40 years.

06:10.638 --> 06:12.139
Well, that's what they say.

06:13.608 --> 06:15.643
You know, when they
first came to Paris,

06:15.676 --> 06:18.079
my father did a special edition
just on him,

06:18.112 --> 06:19.714
put him on the cover.

06:19.747 --> 06:21.515
Yes, I wasn't born yet.

06:22.149 --> 06:23.483
That was the end of The Words.

06:23.517 --> 06:25.553
Yeah. They tried to replace him,

06:25.586 --> 06:27.555
but it was like putting
someone other than Mick Jagger

06:27.588 --> 06:28.990
to front the Stones.

06:30.625 --> 06:31.792
True.

06:31.826 --> 06:33.928
But the point is, Jake is dead.

06:33.961 --> 06:36.697
He jumped into the Seine
in front of a ton of people.

06:37.832 --> 06:38.833
Really well.

06:40.134 --> 06:41.702
And I never understood why

06:41.736 --> 06:44.171
a rock star like him
would commit suicide.

06:45.706 --> 06:47.141
Rock star vertigo, maybe.

06:50.044 --> 06:51.245
Listen, Meg,

06:51.279 --> 06:54.248
do you know anything
about <i>The Phantom of the Opera?</i>

06:54.282 --> 06:57.084
I know it was
a French boring story

06:57.118 --> 06:59.687
we had to learn in school.

06:59.720 --> 07:00.721
Why?

07:02.590 --> 07:03.456
Well, just think about it.

07:03.490 --> 07:05.893
I have a couple
of important meetings,

07:05.927 --> 07:07.595
but I'll meet you here,

07:09.196 --> 07:10.497
at midnight.

07:11.299 --> 07:12.465
The Class.

07:14.235 --> 07:16.570
What the hell is The Class?

07:16.604 --> 07:18.839
Well, you'll find out
when you get there.

07:31.852 --> 07:33.087
<i>♪ The mother</i>

07:34.522 --> 07:36.456
<i>♪ Of the outlaw</i>

07:38.793 --> 07:40.895
<i>♪ Thinks about the time</i>

07:40.928 --> 07:43.864
<i>♪ He had the mumps</i>

07:43.898 --> 07:45.967
<i>♪ And she's really</i>

07:46.634 --> 07:48.903
<i>♪ Very sorry</i>

07:51.038 --> 07:53.240
<i>♪ And she hopes
this has nothing to do</i>

07:53.274 --> 07:55.743
<i>♪ With the way
she brought him up</i>

07:56.711 --> 07:58.179
<i>♪ And the outlaw</i>

07:59.213 --> 08:01.649
<i>♪ He lies wounded</i>

08:03.617 --> 08:08.990
<i>♪ As the doctor gives
the police sergeant a nod</i>

08:09.023 --> 08:11.158
<i>♪ And the last words</i>

08:11.993 --> 08:13.861
<i>♪ He was saying</i>

08:16.063 --> 08:17.698
<i>♪ Something about</i>

08:17.732 --> 08:21.268
<i>♪ I do believe in God</i>

08:21.302 --> 08:23.671
<i>♪ And who</i>

08:23.704 --> 08:26.807
<i>♪ Divides the oceans</i>

08:29.076 --> 08:31.812
<i>♪ When a generation
lost its place</i>

08:33.714 --> 08:36.049
<i>♪ And who</i>

08:36.082 --> 08:38.552
<i>♪ Sets the motion</i>

08:40.821 --> 08:44.759
<i>♪ Of the human race ♪</i>

08:56.604 --> 08:57.838
Rum and Coke, please.

08:58.606 --> 08:59.607
Coming right up.

09:01.175 --> 09:02.576
Are you an actor?

09:04.045 --> 09:05.046
What?

09:05.746 --> 09:07.815
Have you seen me in something?

09:08.315 --> 09:10.117
No, but honestly,

09:10.151 --> 09:13.954
I never knew a bartender
who wasn't an actor.

09:13.988 --> 09:16.757
Do you know
anything about theatre?

09:16.791 --> 09:18.959
I know I've done
a lot of auditions.

09:18.993 --> 09:21.362
So, you know
<i>Phantom of the Opera.</i>

09:21.395 --> 09:23.831
Is it still on Broadway?

09:23.864 --> 09:26.934
Mm. That's one I've never
auditioned for, sorry.

09:26.967 --> 09:28.269
But you know the story.

09:29.937 --> 09:30.938
Let me see.

09:32.807 --> 09:34.175
The Phantom is a guy in a mask

09:34.208 --> 09:36.010
and he lives
in the Paris sewers

09:36.043 --> 09:39.113
when he is not swinging
from Opera chandeliers.

09:39.146 --> 09:41.082
And he is pissed off,

09:41.115 --> 09:43.684
'cause he is a great composer
and he got ripped off.

09:45.286 --> 09:46.287
Or is that <i>Cats?</i>

09:47.321 --> 09:48.622
Uh-huh.

09:49.256 --> 09:50.991
Thanks a lot.

09:51.025 --> 09:52.293
And good luck.

09:52.326 --> 09:53.327
Thanks.

09:57.898 --> 09:58.899
Kathy?

10:00.434 --> 10:01.602
What?

10:03.471 --> 10:04.738
I don't...

10:05.439 --> 10:06.607
Kathy.

10:07.274 --> 10:08.275
Kathy!

10:12.413 --> 10:13.647
Excuse me.

10:15.049 --> 10:17.084
Do you know Plynth the Persian?

10:17.718 --> 10:18.719
Plynth?

10:20.221 --> 10:21.689
That's him right over there.

10:22.256 --> 10:24.024
Hey, Plynth!

10:24.058 --> 10:26.093
Got a lady here
who wants to talk to ya.

10:31.799 --> 10:33.667
Are you Plynth the Persian?

10:33.701 --> 10:35.402
Yeah. What can I do for you?

10:35.436 --> 10:38.005
I just spoke with Kathy Madison
on the phone.

10:38.038 --> 10:41.075
She told me you maybe have
something to tell me?

10:41.108 --> 10:42.743
Oh.

10:42.776 --> 10:44.845
I was talking to her
about Jake Lion.

10:45.479 --> 10:47.848
I was his personal roadie.

10:47.882 --> 10:51.185
Used to help him on stage
when he was too drunk to walk.

10:51.218 --> 10:53.087
And I was with him in The Words

10:53.120 --> 10:54.922
the year he disappeared.

10:54.955 --> 10:55.956
And?

10:57.491 --> 10:58.659
Well,

10:59.193 --> 11:00.427
like I told Kathy,

11:00.895 --> 11:03.097
Jake Lion is alive

11:03.130 --> 11:04.732
and only I know where he is.

11:05.833 --> 11:07.434
That's bullshit.

11:07.468 --> 11:10.871
Jake Lion is dead
for, what, 40 years?

11:11.372 --> 11:12.840
You know, you're cute.

11:12.873 --> 11:14.708
And you're a liar.

11:14.742 --> 11:16.377
I never lie.

11:16.410 --> 11:18.913
Except about the size
of my dick.

11:18.946 --> 11:21.015
So, finally, what's the story?

11:21.782 --> 11:22.783
Well, here it is.

11:23.918 --> 11:26.854
I'm finishing up a European tour
with Vampire Weekend,

11:26.887 --> 11:28.822
and I got a day off in Paris.

11:28.856 --> 11:29.990
<i>I'm on the metro.</i>

11:32.426 --> 11:33.727
Give me a Diet Coke, Rick.

11:35.396 --> 11:37.498
<i>The train pulls into
Pere-Lachaise.</i>

11:37.532 --> 11:40.100
<i>That's the big cemetery.</i>

11:40.134 --> 11:42.436
<i>And I started hearing
Jake Lion's voice.</i>

11:43.404 --> 11:44.405
<i>Loud,</i>

11:45.139 --> 11:46.140
<i>clear,</i>

11:46.807 --> 11:47.908
and live.

11:49.310 --> 11:50.844
And I knew that voice.

11:51.445 --> 11:53.347
<i>It gave me goosebumps.</i>

11:53.380 --> 11:55.249
<i>There was no mistaking it.
It was Jake.</i>

11:55.883 --> 11:57.519
<i>So, you saw a ghost.</i>

11:57.552 --> 11:59.386
<i>Shit like that happens
all the time,</i>

11:59.420 --> 12:01.523
especially when
you are high enough.

12:01.556 --> 12:04.291
I've been sober for 20 years.

12:04.325 --> 12:06.393
And I knew Jake Lion
better than anyone.

12:06.427 --> 12:09.296
But why you didn't
go back to see him?

12:09.330 --> 12:10.965
I did go back the next morning.

12:10.998 --> 12:12.266
Couldn't find him.

12:12.299 --> 12:14.368
Then we left Paris.
I mean, I was on tour.

12:15.970 --> 12:17.972
But maybe it was, I don't know,

12:18.005 --> 12:19.373
someone who wanted to be him

12:19.406 --> 12:22.176
or an imitator.
Or, I don't know...

12:22.209 --> 12:23.777
No way. No way.

12:25.012 --> 12:26.380
I was with Jake Lion
and The Words

12:26.413 --> 12:28.282
until the very end.

12:28.315 --> 12:30.017
Did a three-month tour
around the States

12:30.050 --> 12:31.285
before he split to Paris.

12:32.186 --> 12:33.821
He was planning a new album

12:33.854 --> 12:36.790
and he was writing new songs
like crazy.

12:36.824 --> 12:39.594
And nobody ever heard him sing
those new songs but me.

12:39.628 --> 12:42.263
But, what does
that really prove?

12:43.364 --> 12:44.999
Prove?

12:45.032 --> 12:46.800
He was singing
one of those new songs

12:46.834 --> 12:48.869
when I saw him on the subway.
That's what it proves.

12:48.902 --> 12:51.372
Are you Meg Trudeau,
by any chance?

12:51.405 --> 12:52.773
I am Meg Trudeau.

12:53.207 --> 12:54.341
Why?

12:54.375 --> 12:56.977
Somebody left
something for you earlier.

13:04.485 --> 13:06.387
Tickets for Paris?

13:06.420 --> 13:08.956
Why? I don't want
to go back there.

13:08.989 --> 13:11.025
My God, it's not
my home anymore.

13:12.293 --> 13:13.595
<i>Merde!</i>

13:17.231 --> 13:20.467
<i>♪ You know my secret</i>

13:20.502 --> 13:25.806
<i>♪ In a way
I just try to be free ♪</i>

13:37.117 --> 13:39.453
I just received a message
from Kathy Madison

13:39.486 --> 13:43.057
to come and to see you
before my travelling in Paris.

13:43.090 --> 13:44.191
Good morning, Mr. Springsteen.

13:44.224 --> 13:46.960
Good morning. Welcome to
the great state of New Jersey.

13:46.994 --> 13:47.995
Thank you.

13:48.996 --> 13:51.566
So, it seems Kathy thinks

13:51.599 --> 13:54.468
you can bring Jake Lion
back to life.

13:54.502 --> 13:57.171
That would be a good trick.
He's been gone for quite a while.

13:57.806 --> 14:00.107
But how did you meet him?

14:00.140 --> 14:03.110
We met in the early '70s.

14:03.143 --> 14:05.179
We were probably 22 years old.

14:05.212 --> 14:07.081
Two of us were just kids.

14:07.114 --> 14:09.116
He was with
his group, The Words,

14:09.149 --> 14:10.150
and I was

14:10.918 --> 14:12.186
solo act at the time.

14:12.219 --> 14:14.455
But his style was...

14:14.488 --> 14:16.524
Was more like... I think
they signed the two of us

14:16.558 --> 14:18.292
to be new Dylans together
actually, at the time.

14:18.325 --> 14:20.562
That was <i>Everybody's
Looking For Somebody.</i>

14:20.595 --> 14:23.097
And, uh... Around 1972.

14:24.398 --> 14:26.266
And did you play
some music with him?

14:26.300 --> 14:27.334
Not too much.

14:27.368 --> 14:29.269
Jake let me open for him.

14:29.303 --> 14:30.605
I opened for him a few times.

14:30.638 --> 14:32.039
And... Which was pretty nice

14:32.072 --> 14:33.675
because there wasn't
a lot of people letting us

14:33.708 --> 14:35.242
open for 'em in those days.

14:35.275 --> 14:36.678
- Yes.
- And...

14:36.711 --> 14:40.214
But we hung around together
quite a bit and...

14:40.247 --> 14:42.916
I've... Just somebody
I've felt really close to.

14:42.950 --> 14:44.586
You know, I've missed him.

14:44.619 --> 14:46.621
And, what do you remember
about him?

14:46.654 --> 14:47.988
What do you remember?

14:48.021 --> 14:50.491
What can you tell me
about what was he like?

14:51.125 --> 14:53.060
Jake was...

14:53.093 --> 14:56.096
Even back then, I would say,
he was a little more miserable

14:56.130 --> 14:58.432
than most artists, you know?

14:58.465 --> 14:59.701
But he was a sweet guy.

14:59.734 --> 15:01.969
He always had a...
He had a sweet heart.

15:02.436 --> 15:04.037
And,

15:04.071 --> 15:05.673
an incredible lyricist.

15:05.707 --> 15:07.241
And really,

15:07.274 --> 15:09.176
just a great frontman,
you know?

15:09.209 --> 15:11.513
Really though, my wife actually

15:11.546 --> 15:13.347
<i>knew him better than I did.</i>

15:13.380 --> 15:15.683
<i>'Cause she sang...
Before she sang with the E-Street Band,</i>

15:15.717 --> 15:18.285
<i>she sang backup in Jake's band
for quite a while.</i>

15:18.318 --> 15:21.121
But he just disappeared
like that.

15:21.155 --> 15:23.558
That was one of
the strangest things, you know?

15:23.591 --> 15:25.560
Uh, and the strange...

15:25.593 --> 15:27.327
It was just as he was

15:28.563 --> 15:30.598
becoming really successful.

15:30.632 --> 15:31.999
- Mmm.
- You know?

15:32.032 --> 15:34.736
And, I mean,
it's not for everybody,

15:34.769 --> 15:36.738
but he'd done all the hard work.

15:36.771 --> 15:39.339
- Mm-hmm.
- He had already done the hard work.

15:39.373 --> 15:42.176
And, once he got there,
for some reason,

15:42.209 --> 15:43.678
- he slipped off the map, you know?
- Yeah.

15:43.711 --> 15:45.513
And, I heard it was Paris,

15:45.547 --> 15:47.214
and I heard
he jumped off a bridge.

15:47.247 --> 15:48.482
I don't know
what happened to him.

15:48.516 --> 15:50.350
Yeah, it's really strange.

15:52.186 --> 15:54.522
- Hi, Patti. I'm Meg.
- Hi. Hi, Meg.

15:54.556 --> 15:56.724
I work with Kathy Madison.

15:56.758 --> 15:58.392
I have some questions.

15:58.425 --> 16:02.062
Jake Lion disappeared like that.

16:02.095 --> 16:04.766
Yeah. I hadn't seen him
in a long time,

16:04.799 --> 16:06.967
but, um, I heard that he...

16:07.836 --> 16:10.437
Well, he jumped off a bridge
in Paris.

16:10.471 --> 16:13.407
Um, I wasn't singing with him
at the time.

16:13.440 --> 16:15.409
I had left the band, The Words,

16:15.442 --> 16:17.010
way before that.

16:17.044 --> 16:19.246
So you were not there
when he jumped into the river.

16:19.279 --> 16:20.682
No.

16:20.715 --> 16:23.585
And when was the last time
you saw him?

16:23.618 --> 16:26.420
The last time I saw him,
he was happy.

16:27.120 --> 16:29.557
I think it was more of his...

16:29.591 --> 16:30.792
He didn't like
what came along with it.

16:30.825 --> 16:32.794
Like fame. I think fame felt

16:32.827 --> 16:35.797
very disruptive to him,

16:35.830 --> 16:37.599
and made him go really inward.

16:37.632 --> 16:39.801
But, if we were touring
and on the bus with him,

16:39.834 --> 16:42.804
he'd playing and singing
and having the greatest time.

16:42.837 --> 16:44.037
Yes.

16:44.071 --> 16:45.673
But I heard, mm,

16:45.707 --> 16:48.408
and I saw
in an interview of Jake,

16:48.442 --> 16:51.245
and he said it was easier
for him to confront a failure

16:51.278 --> 16:52.747
than to deal with success.

16:52.780 --> 16:54.381
What do you think about that?

