I don't know what old times
you might be referring to,

34:25.264 --> 34:29.637
and my name
is not Jake either.

34:29.670 --> 34:33.340
So why don't you just get on,
move along,

34:33.373 --> 34:35.475
and go visit
Jim Morrison's grave

34:35.510 --> 34:37.512
with the rest of the tourists?

34:38.045 --> 34:39.581
I am not a tourist,

34:39.614 --> 34:40.815
I'm a journalist.

34:40.848 --> 34:43.717
And I'm here to write a story.

34:43.751 --> 34:46.554
I don't care who you are
or what you do.

34:46.588 --> 34:48.790
And I suppose you're
just one more American

34:48.822 --> 34:51.726
poking her nose
into other people's business.

34:51.759 --> 34:53.493
Now, if you want
to buy me a drink,

34:54.194 --> 34:56.898
I might accept your hospitality.

34:56.931 --> 34:59.901
But if you call me
Jake again,

34:59.934 --> 35:03.638
I might slit
your pretty little throat.

35:03.671 --> 35:06.106
I don't have a lot to lose
at this point.

35:06.641 --> 35:07.875
You got a temper.

35:08.910 --> 35:11.345
- Sometimes.
- Okay.

35:11.378 --> 35:13.615
I'm sorry if I offended you.

35:13.648 --> 35:15.182
Let's start over.

35:15.215 --> 35:16.751
I'm Meg Trudeau,

35:16.784 --> 35:19.821
and I write
for <i>Rolling Stone</i> magazine.

35:19.854 --> 35:22.924
And I think you have a great
voice, whoever you are.

35:23.490 --> 35:25.526
A real music lover, eh?

35:25.560 --> 35:27.494
Yes, I like music,

35:27.528 --> 35:29.262
and I write about music,

35:29.296 --> 35:31.298
especially your kind of music.

35:31.331 --> 35:34.636
Hold on, you've got some kind
of a French accent.

35:34.669 --> 35:36.470
Are you bullshitting me?

35:36.504 --> 35:38.740
Not at all. I am French.

35:38.773 --> 35:41.542
But I work in New York,
I live in New York.

35:41.576 --> 35:43.945
In fact, I wish I was
in New York now.

35:44.779 --> 35:46.581
Well, then I'd say

35:46.614 --> 35:49.349
you're some kind of mixed up,
shook up girl.

35:49.383 --> 35:51.552
Sounds like
the title of a song.

35:51.586 --> 35:53.788
It is. Willy DeVille.

35:53.821 --> 35:56.624
- Dead now.
- Should have known.

35:56.658 --> 35:58.626
You said something
about buying me a drink?

35:58.660 --> 35:59.661
Mm-hmm.

36:00.494 --> 36:01.495
Let's go.

36:02.730 --> 36:03.731
I got it.

36:45.907 --> 36:46.908
What do you want?

37:01.989 --> 37:03.024
Okay.

37:04.759 --> 37:06.627
No, only for today.

37:13.467 --> 37:14.602
Do you know Jake Lion?

37:15.737 --> 37:16.771
I know he's dead.

37:17.471 --> 37:18.906
Buried over there.

37:18.940 --> 37:21.542
Next to his buddy, Jim Morrison.

37:21.576 --> 37:22.442
Like I said,

37:22.476 --> 37:24.979
you can go pay him a visit
if you want.

37:25.012 --> 37:27.882
I'm sure he'd be thrilled
if you sit on his...

37:27.915 --> 37:29.483
grave.

37:29.517 --> 37:31.586
He threw himself into the
Seine, didn't he?

37:32.319 --> 37:33.688
That's right.

37:33.721 --> 37:35.288
But they didn't bring him
to Pere-Lachaise

37:35.322 --> 37:36.924
until a year later.

37:36.958 --> 37:40.293
The river takes its time
burping up its dead.

37:50.037 --> 37:51.906
So,
you seem to know a lot about him.

37:51.939 --> 37:54.642
Jesus Christ!
You almost stabbed me

37:54.675 --> 37:56.376
when I mentioned his name.

37:56.409 --> 37:58.411
I don't like being disturbed
when I'm working.

37:59.346 --> 38:01.549
And there's something else.

38:01.582 --> 38:04.919
Jake Lion, he was my brother.

38:04.952 --> 38:08.388
So, you are the brother
the record company paid off?

38:08.421 --> 38:11.391
I'm the only brother
Jake Lion ever had.

38:11.424 --> 38:14.494
And I drank that money away
a long time ago.

38:14.996 --> 38:17.832
I'm Erik Lion.

38:17.865 --> 38:20.635
- So, what are you doing here?
- What do you think?

38:20.668 --> 38:22.870
Playing my guitar in the metro.

38:22.904 --> 38:25.907
You're not too observant for a journalist, are you?

38:25.940 --> 38:27.975
I've been living in Paris
for 40 years.

38:28.709 --> 38:29.911
Came over

38:29.944 --> 38:32.479
when they finally found
Jake's body.

38:32.513 --> 38:34.414
Someone had to identify it.

38:34.447 --> 38:36.717
And that someone was me,

38:36.751 --> 38:38.786
his brother, Erik.

38:38.820 --> 38:39.821
Got it?

38:40.688 --> 38:41.923
Oh, shit.

38:41.956 --> 38:44.525
This is not going to go
down well at <i>Rolling Stone.</i>

38:44.559 --> 38:46.761
Kathy won't be happy at all.

38:46.794 --> 38:49.362
- Kathy Madison?
- You knew her?

38:49.396 --> 38:51.532
Not me.

38:51.566 --> 38:54.902
But I knew that her and Jake were
more than friends at some point.

38:54.936 --> 38:56.103
Mind you, personally,

38:56.137 --> 38:57.805
I never went
for those rich chicks

38:57.839 --> 38:59.707
pretending to be hippies.

38:59.740 --> 39:02.610
Used to call them
"Trust fund babes."

39:02.643 --> 39:05.646
Funny that Kathy never told me
Jake's brother is alive.

39:05.680 --> 39:08.616
Or maybe I've been dead
a long time too,

39:08.649 --> 39:10.618
'cause no one has heard
from me in years.

39:11.586 --> 39:12.954
I'm like a ghost.

39:24.198 --> 39:26.000
Like the Phantom of the Opera?

39:27.535 --> 39:28.936
Yeah.

39:28.970 --> 39:31.072
Like that guy who put on a mask,

39:31.105 --> 39:32.405
hid from the world,

39:33.207 --> 39:35.076
because he was so fucking ugly

39:36.244 --> 39:37.545
and deformed.

39:38.579 --> 39:39.914
He was a genius

39:40.681 --> 39:42.049
but nobody cared.

39:43.784 --> 39:45.418
And Kathy Madison,

39:45.452 --> 39:47.021
the rock 'n roll heiress,

39:47.054 --> 39:50.057
has sent you here
to find Jake Lion.

39:50.091 --> 39:51.993
What, does she still got
a thing for him?

39:52.026 --> 39:53.694
Or is it just, uh...

39:53.728 --> 39:56.831
necrophilia or some shit?

39:56.864 --> 39:58.900
Someone told us he was alive

39:58.933 --> 40:01.736
and he saw him here, in Paris,

40:01.769 --> 40:03.504
but it might be you
that he saw.

40:04.739 --> 40:06.807
Who told you that crap?

40:07.942 --> 40:09.810
A guy called Plynth.

40:09.844 --> 40:12.146
Apparently, he was a roadie
for The Words.

40:13.648 --> 40:17.885
Plynth the Persian,
Jake's nanny.

40:17.919 --> 40:21.789
He told us that he heard you
singing a song of Jake

40:21.822 --> 40:23.791
that had never been recorded.

40:23.824 --> 40:27.228
In fact, something he wrote
shortly before he died.

40:28.195 --> 40:29.397
Okay.

40:29.429 --> 40:32.233
Now, I'm going to tell you
something very few people know.

40:32.266 --> 40:36.237
It was me who taught Jake
how to write songs,

40:36.270 --> 40:37.705
how to write lyrics,

40:37.738 --> 40:40.508
how to put them with the
chords, all of that shit.

40:40.541 --> 40:43.077
In fact, most of those
The Words songs

40:43.110 --> 40:45.646
were co-composed by both of us.

40:47.782 --> 40:50.584
I knew those songs
better than anybody.

40:51.118 --> 40:52.620
And, in fact,

40:52.653 --> 40:54.522
years after I left the band,

40:54.555 --> 40:57.525
and before Jake killed himself,

40:57.558 --> 41:00.094
he would send me cassettes
of those new songs

41:01.729 --> 41:03.798
to approve or improve.

41:03.831 --> 41:05.800
Don't I have a right
to sing them?

41:05.833 --> 41:09.770
Looks like you
just blew my Pulitzer Prize.

41:10.671 --> 41:11.672
Sorry.

41:13.040 --> 41:15.109
Hey, Max, <i>la note.</i>

41:16.577 --> 41:17.979
So, what now?

41:19.347 --> 41:21.515
I got an idea.

41:21.549 --> 41:25.186
How about the story of Jake Lion
told by his brother?

41:25.219 --> 41:27.688
That wouldn't be
too bad an angle either.

41:30.257 --> 41:34.061
Why the fuck
would I want to do that?

41:35.696 --> 41:38.299
Let his poor soul
rest in peace.

41:39.633 --> 41:41.102
Isn't that what he wanted?

41:41.135 --> 41:42.169
Look,

41:42.203 --> 41:45.973
everybody thinks Jake
went crazy for no reason.

41:46.007 --> 41:49.043
Maybe you could throw
a light on that.

41:49.076 --> 41:51.812
Like a fresh insight
on an old story.

41:52.947 --> 41:56.150
There's nothing fresh
about a dead man.

41:58.052 --> 42:01.188
I'm willing to pay you
for your time.

42:01.222 --> 42:03.991
But that's an insight
that could interest me.

42:05.026 --> 42:06.894
How long are you
going to be here?

42:06.927 --> 42:08.029
Three more days.

42:08.662 --> 42:09.663
Okay.

42:10.598 --> 42:12.166
Here's the deal.

42:12.199 --> 42:14.268
You got three appointments

42:14.301 --> 42:17.004
at the place and the time

42:17.038 --> 42:18.039
I say.

42:20.908 --> 42:22.676
But what you gotta do now...

42:24.645 --> 42:25.713
Alright.

42:38.325 --> 42:40.594
By the way,
do you live near here?

42:41.162 --> 42:42.663
A place I could visit?

42:43.097 --> 42:45.199
No way.

42:45.232 --> 42:48.135
Where I live has got
nothing to do with Jake Lion.

42:48.169 --> 42:50.037
And the last thing I need

42:50.071 --> 42:53.908
is Kathy Madison
knocking on my door.

42:53.941 --> 42:57.378
I was hoping you'd say
that you lived in the cemetery.

42:57.411 --> 42:59.680
Another good angle
for the story.

43:01.015 --> 43:02.349
Brilliant angle.

43:03.751 --> 43:04.752
I gotta go.

43:05.820 --> 43:07.822
What did you say
your name was, again?

43:07.855 --> 43:09.256
Meg Trudeau.

43:10.191 --> 43:12.093
Okay, Meg Trudeau,

43:12.960 --> 43:14.261
I'll see you tomorrow.

43:14.862 --> 43:16.363
Notre-Dame.

43:16.397 --> 43:18.632
In the garden, in the back.

43:18.666 --> 43:20.167
Five o'clock, sharp.

43:20.835 --> 43:22.002
Don't be late.

43:22.036 --> 43:23.637
Don't bring anyone.

43:24.071 --> 43:25.806
And no photos

43:25.840 --> 43:27.141
or I'm gone.

43:29.343 --> 43:31.112
Just one question
before you go.

43:33.147 --> 43:35.349
Come on,
I gave you an advance.

43:39.253 --> 43:40.821
What happened to your legs?

43:42.356 --> 43:43.657
My legs?

43:44.825 --> 43:47.228
I guess I missed my polio shot.

44:16.190 --> 44:17.758
And you believe him?

44:17.791 --> 44:20.060
I mean, I believe
he's not Jake Lion.

44:20.094 --> 44:22.229
This guy's not a rock star,
he never was.

44:22.263 --> 44:25.032
He is just playing
for change in the metro.

44:25.065 --> 44:27.234
But he could be Jake's brother.

44:27.268 --> 44:29.203
The story kind of makes sense.

44:29.236 --> 44:30.371
That's not what I mean.

44:30.404 --> 44:32.439
I mean, how do you know
he's not just some guy

44:32.473 --> 44:34.441
playing the guitar
in the metro,

44:34.475 --> 44:37.811
nothing to do with Jake Lion
or his brother? Just a nobody.

44:37.845 --> 44:39.146
I don't think he is a nobody.

44:39.180 --> 44:41.248
I think he is somebody
with a story to tell.

44:41.282 --> 44:42.716
Are you sure?

44:42.750 --> 44:45.052
I'm not. But actually,
you knew him.

44:45.085 --> 44:47.354
You should come along
with me next time.

44:47.388 --> 44:49.056
No excuses.

44:55.329 --> 44:59.099
<i>♪ Are you feeling
that down today?</i>

44:59.133 --> 45:02.970
<i>♪ Is there nothing
anybody can say?</i>

45:03.003 --> 45:07.308
<i>♪ Is there not one place
where you feel comfortable</i>

45:07.341 --> 45:12.179
<i>♪ Put your feet up
and feel full of what life is?</i>

45:14.248 --> 45:17.851
<i>♪ And are you feeling
that the future has passed?</i>

45:18.520 --> 45:21.989
<i>♪ And left you in its path</i>

45:22.022 --> 45:26.160
<i>♪ Like a hurricane
through a Florida town</i>

45:26.193 --> 45:31.165
<i>♪ Where all the tall trees
just fell down</i>

45:33.434 --> 45:37.438
<i>♪ And are you feeling
that you just can't move</i>

45:37.471 --> 45:41.108
<i>♪ That you got
nothing left to prove</i>

45:41.141 --> 45:43.177
<i>♪ And that you passed
the test</i>

45:43.210 --> 45:45.212
<i>♪ You lasted
longer than the rest</i>

45:45.246 --> 45:47.081
<i>♪ In the open field</i>

45:47.114 --> 45:50.518
<i>♪ Where the lightning
had the best chance</i>

45:52.152 --> 45:53.854
<i>♪ Of getting hit</i>

45:56.290 --> 45:58.158
<i>♪ Of getting blissed-out</i>

45:58.192 --> 46:02.096
<i>♪ In the land of Nod</i>

46:04.031 --> 46:05.933
<i>♪ Of getting blissed-out</i>

46:05.966 --> 46:09.203
<i>♪ In the land of Nod</i>

46:12.006 --> 46:13.440
<i>♪ Of getting blissed-out</i>

46:13.474 --> 46:15.342
<i>♪ In the land</i>

46:16.343 --> 46:19.046
<i>♪ Blissed-out in the land</i>

46:20.114 --> 46:22.449
<i>♪ Blissed-out in the land</i>

46:23.417 --> 46:25.052
<i>♪ Of Nod ♪</i>

46:51.613 --> 46:53.047
You frightened me.

46:53.080 --> 46:54.381
I've been waiting an hour.

46:54.915 --> 46:56.350
I've always been here.

46:56.383 --> 46:58.952
I tried to blend in
with the gargoyles,

46:59.887 --> 47:01.322
on top of the church.

47:01.355 --> 47:04.358
- Do you mind if I record our conversation?
- Oh, no.

47:04.391 --> 47:06.093
- No way.
- Why not?

47:07.394 --> 47:08.596
Liabilities.

47:08.630 --> 47:10.097
Liabilities of what?

47:10.898 --> 47:13.367
Claims, lawsuits.

47:13.400 --> 47:16.303
You know,
sometimes I drink too much.

47:16.337 --> 47:17.471
Really?

47:18.072 --> 47:20.274
You could have fooled me.

47:21.175 --> 47:25.245
And I might say something
I shouldn't say.

47:25.279 --> 47:28.248
And if that goes down
on a tape recorder...

47:29.917 --> 47:32.319
You remember what happened
to President Nixon.

47:32.353 --> 47:33.555
What happened to Nixon?

47:35.322 --> 47:36.924
No. Nothing.

47:36.957 --> 47:40.194
Okay. I'll try to get down
everything you say

47:40.227 --> 47:42.062
as accurately I can.

47:42.597 --> 47:45.332
I hope I can at least

47:46.133 --> 47:48.369
take some notes?

47:48.402 --> 47:50.904
Yeah, as long
as there is no microphone

47:50.938 --> 47:52.239
hidden in your pen.

47:52.272 --> 47:54.609
One, two, three.

47:56.076 --> 47:57.277
So,

47:57.311 --> 47:59.179
what did Jake look like

47:59.213 --> 48:02.116
when you went
to identify his body?

48:02.149 --> 48:03.217
Hmm.

48:04.184 --> 48:05.486
Nice first question.

48:07.555 --> 48:11.959
Well, let's just say that
being underwater for a year

48:11.992 --> 48:14.161
didn't do much
for his complexion.

48:16.296 --> 48:18.332
<i>Not much was left of his face.</i>

48:18.365 --> 48:20.334
<i>But he broke his arm
when we were kids,</i>

48:20.367 --> 48:21.603
<i>fell from a tree.</i>

48:21.636 --> 48:23.904
<i>And I could still see
the scar there.</i>

48:24.606 --> 48:26.206
<i>So, that kind of nailed it,</i>

48:26.240 --> 48:28.375
<i>and I signed off
on some bullshit papers,</i>

48:28.409 --> 48:31.178
<i>put his body in my backpack,
and walked out.</i>

48:31.211 --> 48:32.312
<i>Really?</i>

48:32.346 --> 48:34.649
<i>No. Jesus Christ.</i>

48:35.617 --> 48:38.185
<i>We buried him in Pere-Lachaise</i>

48:38.218 --> 48:41.523
'cause his friend said
he liked to hang out there.

48:41.556 --> 48:43.625
I think the record company
pulled some strings

48:43.658 --> 48:44.793
to get him in there.

48:44.826 --> 48:48.262
And when that was all done,
you just stayed in Paris?

48:48.295 --> 48:52.266
Because there was no reason
to go home again.

48:52.299 --> 48:54.569
The United States
is not the best place

48:55.436 --> 48:57.971
for a disabled person.

48:58.005 --> 49:01.141
If you're not Superman,
you're kind of screwed.

49:01.709 --> 49:03.745
I inherited his guitar,

49:05.547 --> 49:08.750
and the record company gave me
some cash to keep me quiet.

49:08.783 --> 49:10.184
Quiet about what?

49:10.217 --> 49:12.453
Oh, I mean, I signed off
on his royalties,

49:12.486 --> 49:14.354
promised not to
bother them anymore.

49:15.222 --> 49:17.291
And Paris became your home.

49:18.827 --> 49:20.227
A home

49:21.495 --> 49:24.064
implies some kind of stability,

49:24.699 --> 49:26.033
so I wouldn't say that.

49:27.434 --> 49:29.336
Come on, let's take a walk.

49:32.507 --> 49:34.441
Do your legs bother you?

49:34.475 --> 49:37.712
No, but sitting next to
this damn church does.

49:52.493 --> 49:54.796
So, what kind of guy was Jake?

49:56.096 --> 49:57.097
Jake?

49:57.765 --> 49:59.199
He didn't say much

49:59.868 --> 50:01.368
even when he was a kid.

50:03.070 --> 50:05.105
But I remember him saying
to me once

50:05.573 --> 50:06.708
that his songs

50:07.742 --> 50:09.677
knew more about him

50:09.711 --> 50:11.846
than he knew about his songs.

50:13.615 --> 50:16.784
For some reason,
I imagined him as a tough guy.

50:16.818 --> 50:19.554
But things got to him
all the same.

50:19.587 --> 50:22.356
I mean, don't things
get to everyone?

50:23.390 --> 50:24.526
You know,

50:24.559 --> 50:26.126
to be a rock star,

50:26.794 --> 50:28.495
you need strong ears

50:28.963 --> 50:30.497
and a thick skin.

50:31.498 --> 50:33.768
But brains, talent...

50:34.869 --> 50:36.236
that's optional.

50:37.672 --> 50:41.375
So, what's so great
about playing in the metro?

50:42.610 --> 50:46.346
What's so great about playing
in Madison Square Garden?

50:46.380 --> 50:48.650
Did you ever play
in Madison Square Garden?

50:49.817 --> 50:51.619
<i>Uh, no. Not me.</i>

50:53.120 --> 50:54.622
<i>But I saw Jake play there.</i>

50:56.758 --> 51:00.460
<i>And all he could see
was the first four rows.</i>

51:00.494 --> 51:03.230
And that was full
of music business people.

51:03.765 --> 51:06.433
And he didn't like that.

51:06.466 --> 51:10.103
Well, Jake said that when you
first get into the business,

51:10.137 --> 51:12.540
you know, you're so impressed

51:12.574 --> 51:14.642
by these big shot executives

51:15.475 --> 51:16.544
'cause you think

51:17.311 --> 51:18.880
they control your life.

51:20.147 --> 51:21.381
But then,

51:21.415 --> 51:23.083
one day you realize

51:23.918 --> 51:25.687
you want to play
for the real people.

51:27.187 --> 51:29.791
Are you talking about you
or about Jake now?

51:33.160 --> 51:34.494
What's the difference?

51:38.700 --> 51:41.903
There is no music
without business.

51:41.936 --> 51:44.639
Sounds like a typical
loser's philosophy to me.

51:45.974 --> 51:48.141
You know what?

51:48.175 --> 51:50.612
I think you're trying
to provoke me.

51:51.779 --> 51:53.246
That was Jake's thing.

51:53.781 --> 51:55.282
I was never into that.

51:55.950 --> 51:59.654
So, Jake wanted the stardom.

51:59.687 --> 52:03.725
Well, he fell for the glitter
and the gloom like they all do.

52:06.561 --> 52:11.231
But what he couldn't stand
were the inconsistencies.

52:12.867 --> 52:15.603
<i>He told me he'd be onstage</i>

52:15.637 --> 52:18.573
<i>singing for
thousands of people,</i>

52:18.606 --> 52:21.576
<i>and then he'd be back home,
in a hotel,</i>

52:21.609 --> 52:23.945
<i>trying to find something
to watch on TV.</i>

52:25.747 --> 52:28.248
Said he couldn't stop
the screaming

52:28.750 --> 52:29.917
in his ears.

52:53.708 --> 52:56.476
Hey, <i>bonjour,</i> my friend.

